  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "=General= Varied crag climbing, 3–7 metres high, with plenty of easier routes. A long fault-line crag and several boulders.\n\n=Directions= 2 km south-east of Jägarhyddan. From Rimbo, take road 280 to the sign for Södertjära and turn right. Continue for just over 1 km, passing a sharp right-hand bend with a barn on the right, then park on the right at the top of the hill. Continue a little further along the road as it bends left and up to the crest. Spetsblocket is then visible straight ahead. Follow the forest track into the woods until it forks by an attractive mushroom-shaped boulder (with hard projects). Take the right-hand path. About 100 m before a house, a smaller path branches off to the left. Follow this until the long fault-line crag comes into view. About a pleasant 10-minute walk from the parking.\n\n=Sectors=",
